# Both images build from the REPO ROOT, because each composes files from more than one lane:
#   ingest    backend/ingest/app (C) + db/exports.py (A)
#   nightly   backend/jobs (A) + db/exposure.py (A) + backend/mapmatch/valhalla.py (C) + contracts/
#
# A root context is dangerous by default — this repo holds multi-GB Valhalla tiles and OSM extracts
# (backend/mapmatch/data), plus .git and venvs, none of which must ever be shipped to the daemon.
# Note valhalla.py sits right next to that data, so precision matters here.
#
# So: exclude everything, then re-include exactly what the images need. Deny-by-default means a new
# large directory can't silently bloat the build.
*

# ingest image
!backend/ingest/requirements.txt
!backend/ingest/app/
!db/exports.py

# nightly pipeline image
!backend/jobs/requirements.txt
!backend/jobs/nightly.py
!backend/jobs/aggregate.py
!backend/jobs/config/
!db/exposure.py
!backend/mapmatch/valhalla.py
!contracts/mapmatch.py

# ...and never let build artefacts ride along inside the re-included paths (these rules come last,
# so they win over the re-includes above).
**/__pycache__/
**/*.pyc
**/.pytest_cache/
